  "local_port": 49012,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm turning 21 today. What advice do you have for me?",
  "response": "Happy Birthday! Turning 21 is a significant milestone\u2014it\u2019s a time of transition, growth, and new opportunities. Here\u2019s some advice to make the most of this exciting phase of your life:\n\n### **Personal Growth & Self-Discovery**\n1. **Get to Know Yourself**  \n   Take time to understand your values, passions, and goals. Journal, reflect, and experiment with new hobbies or interests.\n2. **Embrace Failure**  \n   Mistakes are part of the learning process. Don\u2019t fear them; use them as opportunities to grow.\n3. **Prioritize Your Mental Health**  \n   Take care of your mind as much as your body. Practice self-care, seek help when needed, and build healthy routines.\n\n### **Relationships**\n4. **Surround Yourself With Good People**  \n   Build relationships with people who inspire, support, and challenge you. Quality over quantity.\n5. **Learn to Communicate**  \n   Honest, open communication is key to healthy relationships\u2014whether with friends, family, or romantic partners.\n6. **Let Go of Toxic Relationships**  \n   It\u2019s okay to distance yourself from people who drain your energy or hold you back.\n\n### **Finances**\n7. **Start Saving & Budgeting**  \n   Even a small amount saved now can grow significantly over time. Learn to manage your money wisely.\n8. **Avoid Debt When Possible**  \n   Be mindful of credit cards and loans. Spend within your means and prioritize paying off debts.\n9. **Invest in Yourself**  \n   Spend money on experiences, education, or skills that will benefit you in the long run.\n\n### **Health & Wellness**\n10. **Take Care of Your Body**  \n    Eat well, exercise regularly, and get enough sleep. Your health is your greatest asset.\n11. **Drink Responsibly**  \n    If you choose to drink, do so in moderation. Stay safe and know your limits.\n12. **Stay Active**  \n    Find a form of exercise you enjoy\u2014it\u2019s a great way to boost your mood and energy.\n\n### **Career & Goals**\n13. **Set Goals, But Stay Flexible**  \n    Have a vision for your future, but be open to new opportunities and changes along the way.\n14. **Build Skills**  \n    Invest in learning new skills, whether through formal education, online courses, or hands-on experience.\n15. **Network & Seek Mentors**  \n    Build connections with people in your field and learn from those who have been where you want to go.\n\n### **Life in General**\n16. **Travel & Explore**  \n    If you can, travel to new places. It\u2019s a great way to broaden your perspective and create lasting memories.\n17. **Be Present**  \n    Enjoy the moment. Life moves fast, and it\u2019s easy to get caught up in the future or the past.\n18. **Give Back**  \n    Volunteer or help others when you can. It\u2019s a rewarding way to connect with your community and make a difference.\n19. **Trust the Process**  \n    Life doesn\u2019t always go as planned, and that\u2019s okay. Embrace the journey and trust that things will work out.\n20. **Celebrate Yourself**  \n    Be proud of how far you\u2019ve come and excited for what\u2019s ahead. You\u2019re just getting started!\n\nHere\u2019s to an amazing year ahead\u2014enjoy every moment of it! \ud83c\udf89",
  "temperature": 1.0,
